@NODE "Config" "Config"
@TOC "MAIN"
Open the config window.

User  Color (def:Cyan )  - The color of the users text in a chat.
SysOp Color (def:White)  - The color of the sysops in a chat.
Msg's Color (def:Cyan )  - The color of 'System Message' and 'Option' which
                           are shown when sending a message.
Line Color  (def:Blue )  - The color of the lines which are printed when
                           sending a message.
Text Color  (def:White)  - The color of the text in the sending.

Nordic Address (def:on ) - If on it will display the user info with the 
                           standard Scandinavian address system, if off it
                           will add the county name before the country name.
Force Text     (def:off) - If on it will print out the message at once, if
                           off then the message will be shown when the user
                           updates it's menu.

Header  - The text which is shown just before the sysop breaks in to chat.
          If empty, nothing will be shown before the chat.
Footer  - The text which is shown when the sysop breaks the chat.
          If empty, nothing will be shown after a chat break.
Exe Com - The command which will be executed when ChatVoyeur recives the
          EXECUTE command via it's Arexx port. If empty, no command will
          be executed.

Save - Saves the configuration.
Use  - exit the config.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "about" "about"
@TOC "MAIN"
Some information about CANDYWARE and the author.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "quit" "quit"
@TOC "MAIN"
Quit's ChatVoyeur.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "chat" "chat"
@TOC "MAIN"
Start/Exit chat with the user on the current line. This with the help
of Zeus:Bin/Chat.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "hangup" "hangup"
@TOC "MAIN"
Runs the Zeus:Bin/BootUser program, which throws out the user from
the BBS.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "name" "name"
@TOC "MAIN"
The name of the user of the current line.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "action" "action"
@TOC "MAIN"
What the user on the current line is doing.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "req" "req"
@TOC "MAIN"
The message which has been sent to ChatVoyeur from an @{"arexx" LINK "arexx"} script.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "msg" "msg"
@TOC "MAIN"
The one line high 'full screen' message editor. You can write a message 
which has 255 or less characters (return is one character as space). You can
write one 255 character long line or 255 lines, 0 characters long text or 
anything between those two. Use the cursor buttons to move on the lines.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "send" "send"
@TOC "MAIN"
Send the message which has been written and then clears the @{"message" LINK "msg"} gadget.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "text" "text"
@TOC "MAIN"
Opens a file requester and shows the contents of it for the user.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "file" "file"
@TOC "MAIN"
Opens a file requester and send the file to the user with the users
choosen transfere protocol.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "speed" "speed"
@TOC "MAIN"
Shows the users current speed.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "level" "level"
@TOC "MAIN"
Shows the users access level.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "line" "line"
@TOC "MAIN"
Shows the current line from which you get all information.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "<" "<"
@TOC "MAIN"
Jumps down a line, if it's the first line, then it will jump to the last 
line.

@ENDNODE

@NODE ">" ">"
@TOC "MAIN"
Jumps up a line, if it's the last line, then it will jump to the first line.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "inf" "inf"
@TOC "MAIN"
Show the users @{"address" LINK "Config"} and the amount uploads/downloads and free downloads.
The first value is the amount of bytes, the other is the amount of files.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "edit" "edit"
@TOC "MAIN"
Starts the user editor (Zeus:Utils/UserEdit), it loads the current user.
If there isn't any user on the current line, then it will only start the
user editor without loadin any user.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "arexx" "arexx"
@TOC "MAIN"
ChatVoyeur has a arexx port called CVPORT, this prevents the use of more
than one copy of the program, and it supports 5 arexx commands and they are

 CHAT x str
  x is the number of the line, str is the string. The string will be shown
  in the @{"Chat Req" LINK "req"} gadget. ChatVoyeur will change to the line x.

  eg: rx "ADDRESS CVPORT CHAT 1 'Hello SysOp!'"


 CLEAR x
  x is the line which Chat Req you want to remove.

  eg: rx "ADDRESS CVPORT CLEAR 1"

 
 BEEP
  This command will call on the dipslaybeep function. What will happen
  depends on your Prefs/Sound settings.

  eg: rx "ADDRESS CVPORT BEEP"


 EXECUTE
  This command will force ChatVoyeur to execute the @{"'Exe Com'" LINK "Config"} line.

  eg: rx "ADDRESS CVPORT EXECUTE"


 QUIT
  Quit's ChatVoyeur

 eg: rx "ADDRESS CVPORT QUIT"


@ENDNODE

@NODE "CV" "CV"
@TOC "MAIN"
ChatVoyeur v1.02  ® 1996 Trizt of Ward

This is a CANDYWARE and if you want to know what that is, then you have
to run ChatVoyeur and read the about text.


Why make this program when there is Voyeur for Zeus?

 On the version of Zeus which I saw there was not any good 'sysop pager'
 so I gott an assignment to make a working one, so I did. First I thought
 of makeing only a display gadget for chat requests with the ability to
 use the displaybeep(). Butt then I discovered that when you iconified the
 Voyeur it did prevent any future logins on the current line and some days
 later I saw the new SendToLine, so I gott the idea to make one program
 which did all those things and which wouldn't stop a line (it's why Chat-
 Voyeur can't be iconified) and whit some other nice features.
 

Requerments

 Amiga with OS2.0 or better
 Asl.library         37+
 Zeus.library        37+
 Rexxsyslib.library
 A lot of candy


Future versions

 Dont realy know if I will make updates of ChatVoyeur, I have other plans,
 but if there is a demand of a new version sometime in the future then maybe.


Bugreports

 If you discover a bug, send a small bugreport to: md4aho@mdstud.chalmers.se

@ENDNODE

